During the course the knowledge of the character and history of the Islamic Studies as a research discipline will be attained, the history of the older Arabic religion and Islam and the contents of Koran focusing on the relevance of it and other texts for the persistence and diversity of Islam (incl. the relation to the Bible) will be studied, and the ability of finding and using Reference works and relevant secondary literature will be trained.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives an overview of the Islamic Studies as a research discipline and of the development of Islam as a religion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student:  1) understands the Islamic Studies as a research discipline; 2) knows the character and history of the Islamic Studies; 3) orientates in the history of the older Arabic religion and Islam; 4) can outline the contents of Koran; 5) understands the relevance of Koran and other texts for the persistence and diversity of Islam (incl. the relation to the Bible); 6) can find and use Reference works and relevant secondary literature.
